    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="306" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <head>No. 306.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">West</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-07-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 30,
                                1883</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Acknowledging the receipt of your note of
                            the 25th instant concerning the alleged stealing of horses from Canadian
                            territory by South Piegan Indians from the United States, I have the
                            honor to inform you that the proper authorities of this Government have
                            been requested to investigate the matter, with a view to having such
                            action taken as may be found to be proper.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
